The article discusses the author's support for the Indian Child Welfare Act (ICWA) and celebrates a recent Supreme Court decision that upholds the law. The ICWA is aimed at protecting the future of Tribal Nations and promoting the best interests of Native children. It respects tribal sovereignty and helps Native families stay together, prioritizing placement with extended family or community members who understand their cultural identity. The article highlights the historical context of Native children being taken from their families, with the ICWA serving as a promise to prevent such cruelty. The author pledges to continue supporting the ICWA and working with Tribal Nations to protect Native children and uphold tribal sovereignty.